<br>
With the advent of the Bazaar and the already saturated market on Cazic-Thule, I have been able to acquire gear that rivals what I had after two years of hard playing ... and I’m only level 13. Somehow I’ve managed to twink myself beyond recognition, and in the space of a few levels I’ve gone from ho-hum damage to blender-izer. It was fun he first few high blues I soloed, and my group appreciated the extra damage output ... but suddenly the newness, the sense of wonder at having quest armor I *earned*, it was all gone. I realized that all I needed was levels that would be boring to get, and even if I did get them I could never hunt with my friends who are all 60. I came back to EQ to re-enjoy the lower levels.<br>
<br>
I started back on Cazic-Thule because that’s where my friends were, and I spend more time chatting than I do hunting. I have a little bard on Firiona Vie who I loved playing, but it was just so dratted lonely. With the severwide.bards channel, I got to asking, and it seems that cross-server chat is now possible. If I could talk to my old friend as meet new ones in the RP server environment - that would be the best of both worlds.<br>
<br>
1) Is it possible to chat cross-server reliably, with friends on Server X while you’re on Server Y? If this is possible, how do you do this?<br>
2) Bards on FV – are there many of them? The idea of having *only one* character really appeals to me, as there will be few if any twinks. Are there any or many new folks on all classes coming in, or will I never be able to find a group?<br>
3) Guilds on FV – are there any that are bard-friendly? Who accept new members, or aren’t uber? That don’t require you to be level X before you’re accepted?<br>
4) RPing on FV – does anyone really role-play, or are most of you there for the added challenge the server provides?<br>
<br>
Thank you in advance. <p><center>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=311512"> Kelleh Secondsong<br>"I am not an Alt!"</a> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upentapod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pentapod</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/graphics/a_pod.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>WTB phat newt</span><br>  Posts: 443<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/28/02 8:20:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2448.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/miscpics/couple.jpg height=200 width=100.gif></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Firiona Vie and Cross-Server Chatting</span><hr size=1> Cross server chat - yes, it does work, though I haven't done it myself as this is the only server I play on.  You can create your own channel too and have people from other servers in it.<br>
<br>
Bards - there are some, you see them around, I can't say how many but there are definitely bards of all ranks about.<br>
<br>
Guilds - check out the 'guilds and associations' section on these boards, also at the bottom of the main page you'll see the Firiona Vie ezboard ring, this contains links to most of the main guilds on the server, poke around and visit places.  The more 'uber' guilds at the moment are Fire and Fury, Resolution, Dreadstorm, and Awakened Souls.  Other guild requirements vary, my own guild has a 20th rank minimum but many have lower requirements and some have none (e.g. Twilight Bastion I believe).  One good thing to check would be what guilds are around at the times you play - because the server population is so low, you'll want a guild that has people around when you are.  Visit some guild boards, make a note of the ones that sound nice, then do a who all ... during your normal hours.<br>
<br>
RP'ing ... there are always d00dz with us, alas.  But, you'll find more RP'ers here than on other servers, particularly once you reach higher ranks - those not interested will tend to fall away and go back to other servers while still young.  You'll also find that if you RP, you're more likely to be RP'd back to.  Some newbie areas are always worse than others, of course.  Kelethin tends to be bad on any server.  Nektulos can be a bit mixed.  I've found Steamfont to be quite good in terms of RP'ing young ones.  And so on.<br>
<br>
