<br>
The introduction of the Freeport armors only exacerbated the situation.  Not to take anything away from my human and half-breed cohorts, but the pinnacle of bardic excellence has been, and always will be, the throaty, soulful, pine-fresh songs of Kelethin.  Now, there is enough shiny metal pants for the youngsters to re-consider their profession in time to fill our ranks.<br>
<br>
There are bards all over the place, and I can't think of many groups that would not like a Blue Swiss Army Knife in their back pocket - ESPECIALLY after you learn your mana songs.<br>
<br>
As for guilds, I can speak for a few good uns, like the Chosen of Vah (mainly Vah Shir, but not limited), the Twilight Bastion, and my own Ledenyetz Troupe (good-neutral, only wood elves and the collected mini-races).  On the evil side, I can point out a few excellent dens of depravity (most named above) but can't speak for their requirements - only the quality of the members I have met. <p><div align="center">
